cs.SI, cs.SD, cs.LG, cs.DS, cs.SY

Reasoning: 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is the most likely category as the paper deals with temporal social networks and dissemination processes.
- cs.SD (Software Engineering) is also a possible category as the paper proposes a framework for lifting standard graph kernels to the temporal domain, which can be relevant to software engineering.
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is another possible category as the paper proposes a supervised graph classification method using temporal information.
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is a possible category as the paper proposes stochastic variants of the kernels with provable approximation guarantees, which can be relevant to data structures and algorithms.
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper deals with modeling and controlling dissemination processes on temporal graphs.
